name: tree
description: * Create a brand new `PseudoQueue` class. Do not use an existing Queue. Instead, this PseudoQueue class will implement our standard queue interface (the two methods listed below), but will internally only utilize 2 Stack objects. Ensure that you create your class with the following methods:   * `enqueue(value)` which inserts value into the PseudoQueue, using a first-in, first-out approach.   * `dequeue` which extracts a value from the PseudoQueue, using a first-in, first-out approach.
author: HN
